
[1]scouring

   SCOUR'ING, ppr. Rubbing hard with something rough; cleaning by rubbing;
   cleansing with a drastic cathartic; ranging over for clearing.

   SCOUR'ING, n. A rubbing hard for cleaning; a cleansing by a drastic
   purge; looseness; flux.
